column1: # TITLE: RMBL Warming Experiment Fungal Symbiont Diversity
# AUTHOR ADDRESS: University of Vermont; 109 Carrigan Drive; Marsh Life Science Building; Burlington VT 05405
# COLLABORATORS: Jennifer A. Rudgers;  Stephanie N. Kivlin; D. Lee Taylor

# FUNDING SOURCES: National Science Foundation (grant DEB- 1354972); Rocky Mountain Biological Laboratory (National Science Foundation grants DBI-0753774 and OIA-0963529); University of New Mexico Department of Biology
# SAMPLING LOCATIONS: Warming Experiment - Rocky Mountain Biological Laboratory - Gothic CO (38.95806��_N; 106.9894��_W; elev. 2920 m)
# SAMPLING TIMES: June sampling occurred on 30 June and 2 July 2014. September sampling occurred on 25-30 September 2014
# ID: Unique numerical identifier assigned to each sample
# Plot: Number of the plot in the RMBL warming experiment from which the sample was collected.
# WarmingTreatment: Warming treatment of each plot. Warmed plots have infrared lamps suspended over them; control plots are unheated.
# HostSpecies: Grass species from which the sample was collected. AL = Achnatherum lettermanii; FT = Festuca thurberi; PP = Poa pratensis.
# TissueType: Grass tissue type of the sample (roots or leaves).
# CollectionDate: Time of year at which the sample was collected (June or September).
# DivShann: Shannon diversity of fungal symbionts in the sample. Calculated from Illumina paired-end sequencing of the ITS2 region.
# Richness: Fungal symbiont richness of the sample (for leaf samples only). Calculated from Illumina paired-end sequencing of the ITS2 region.
# Evenness: Fungal symbiont evenness of the sample (for leaf samples only). Calculated from Illumina paired-end sequencing of the ITS2 region.
# MISSING DATA: One or more lines for each variable describing the source of NA values throughout
# DATA TRACK CHANGES LOG (use this section to record any changes to the data set after it is created)
